Manchester City's players had plenty to celebrate on Saturday night after beating Crystal Palace to go level on points with Chelsea at the top of the Premier League table.

Manuel Pellegrini's men let their hair down at Italian restaurant Gusto with their wives and girlfriends just hours after their victory at the Etihad.

Frank Lampard was joined by his TV presenter fiancee Christine Bleakley, while goalscorers against the Eagles, Yaya Toure and David Silva, were also in attendance. 

