Two goals from Silva and another from Toure had given City a comfortable win against Palace hours earlier, a result which moved them level on 39 points with Jose Mourinho's side.

Chelsea will look to regain their three-point advantage at the top of the table with victory at Stoke on Monday night, while City's players will now concentrate on a Boxing Day trip to West Brom. 

Pellegrini's men then face two homes in quick succession against Burnley and Sunderland as the busy festive period rolls on, before an FA Cup third round tie with Championship side Sheffield Wednesday at the Etihad.

